# .gitattributes
#
# Forces LF line endings for all text files regardless of the checkout
# platform's core.autocrlf setting.
#
# Root cause this fixes: this repo had no .gitattributes at all. On
# Windows, Git commonly defaults to (or a contributor's global config has)
# core.autocrlf=true, which rewrites LF -> CRLF on checkout for every
# text file. frontend/.prettierrc.json sets "endOfLine": "lf", so any file
# re-saved by a Windows editor after that CRLF checkout gets flagged by
# `prettier --check` in CI ("Code style issues found ... run --write to
# fix") even when nothing meaningful about the file actually changed --
# only its line endings did. Forcing eol=lf here makes Git itself
# normalise line endings on checkout/checkin, so this class of failure
# cannot recur regardless of any individual contributor's local Git config.
#
# After adding this file, existing working-tree files must be
# renormalised once (see the T-061-hardening workflow doc's step 3.3):
#   git add --renormalize .

* text=auto eol=lf

# Explicit binary types -- never touched by line-ending normalisation.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.pdf binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf binary
*.eot binary